  "text": "Prior studies of Phytophthora spp. identified core promoter elements [CITATION_1] with a fair degree of conservation in other oomycetes [CITATION_2] . These include the 7-nt Initiator (INR), 7-nt FPR, and 7-nt DPEP elements. Frequently, the INR and FPR elements [CITATION_3] co-occur in a 16-nt INR + FPR supra-motif. All of these elements were present in Pl. halstedii ( Fig. 6b and c) . However, the motifs were less frequently detected in Pl. halstedii compared to Ph. infestans. For instance, the INR + FPR supra-motif was detected two times less in the downy mildew. A similar reduction in the frequency of this element was observed in Hy. arabidopsidis.",
